cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper discusses methods for text summarization, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP), a subfield of CS.CL.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): Text summarization is closely related to information retrieval, as both involve extracting relevant information from large amounts of text. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Many of the methods discussed in this paper involve machine learning techniques, such as deep learning and reinforcement learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Text summarization is a common application of AI, and many of the methods discussed in this paper fall under the umbrella of AI research. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): While not as directly related as the other categories, this paper does touch on the societal implications of biomedical text summarization, such as the potential for improving medical research and patient care.
